    <p>Lego’s Build To Give</p>
    <p>Share Lego cre­ations on Face­book and In­sta­gram with the fol­low­ing hash­tags – #Re­buildTheWo­rld, #BuildToGiv­eSG and #Lego – and set the posts to pub­lic. For ev­ery 50 sub­mis­sions re­ceived, the Lego Group will give away $2,000 worth of prod­ucts to chil­dren ben­e­fi­cia­ries of se­lected lo­cal char­i­ties. Part of the com­pany’s Re­build the World cam­paign, which cel­e­brates and seeks to nur­ture the nat­u­ral cre­ativ­ity of chil­dren.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Nov 15</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/3oduS0n</p>
    <p>Voices Of Light Vir­tual Char­ity Con­cert</p>
    <p>St Luke’s Hos­pi­tal is or­gan­is­ing a vir­tual fund-rais­ing con­cert fea­tur­ing per­for­mances by ac­com­plished so­prano-soloist Lauren Yeo; vi­o­lin­ist Yap Shu Mei, a for­mer mem­ber of the Sin­ga­pore Sym­phony Orches­tra; and singer-song­writer Crys­tal Goh. All pro­ceeds will go to­wards car­ing for the hos­pi­tal’s low-in­come pa­tients. WHEN: Nov 6, 8.30 – 9.15pm</p>
    <p>ADMISSION: One com­pli­men­tary admission for ev­ery $500 do­na­tion</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/2HmiZEJ</p>


